          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>When everything's nearly ready, add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>cornflour </strong>and your<strong> curry powder</strong> to a<strong> </strong>small bowl with your <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Gradually stir in<strong> </strong>140ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[180ml]</span> [ <span class=\"text-danger\">[240ml]<strong> </span>boiled water </strong>(this is to ensure there's no lumps!) – this is your <strong>curry sauce mix</strong></p><p>Put the <strong>curry sauce</strong> <strong>mix</strong> in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until thickened, stirring half way – this is your <strong>curry sauce</strong></p>",
